    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "Ce workflow joue le rôle de worker.\nIl dépile un job depuis Redis, normalise les données du job, passe le statut à processing, télécharge le PDF depuis MinIO, exécute le traitement, puis met à jour le statut en done ou failed dans PostgreSQL.",
        "height": 352,
        "width": 800,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -976,
        416
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "id": "1c0afad8-9fb1-4664-b93f-1868da1895d8",
      "name": "Sticky Note"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "End-to-End Async PDF Processing & RAG Pipeline (n8n + Redis + MinIO + PGVector)\n\nThis template implements a scalable asynchronous PDF processing pipeline.\n\nWorkflow 1 handles file ingestion: it receives a PDF via webhook, uploads it to MinIO (S3-compatible storage), creates a tracking record in PostgreSQL, and pushes a job into a Redis queue.\n\nWorkflow 2 acts as a worker: it consumes jobs from Redis, updates job status to processing, downloads the PDF, extracts and processes its content, and stores results in PostgreSQL.\n\nThe pipeline supports error handling, status tracking, and can be extended with vector embeddings and RAG-based retrieval.",
        "height": 336,
        "width": 576,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        0,
        -368
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "id": "6bb43fa4-2b30-4090-87fe-4082becf823d",
      "name": "Sticky Note1"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
